      "lesson title": "Cyber Risks in Smart Construction Sites",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Modern construction sites are increasingly relying on connected technologies such as sensors, drones, building management systems, and IoT devices to improve efficiency and safety. However, each new connected device or system introduces a potential entry point for cyber attackers, significantly expanding the attack surface across the site. This lesson explores the key cyber risks that arise when traditional construction environments become \"smart,\" and explains why these risks matter even to those without a technical background. You will learn to recognise common vulnerabilities, understand how a cyberattack could disrupt operations or compromise safety, and take away practical steps to help protect your site. No prior cybersecurity knowledge is required, just an openness to understanding how digital threats are becoming a very real part of modern construction.",
